      "id": "721198521068906",
      "score": 5,
      "review_title": "Genuine review of this game from day 1",
      "review_description": "Edit: Changed to 5 stars because most of these bugs are patched:              \nI'm going to be completely honest. This game has a lot of bugs. A LOT. Considering that this is the first day this game came out, it is pretty good. I can't stop playing, gathering as much loot as possible. I'm making friends and enemies along the way, and working together with people I see. If you want this game to stay at a good rating, you have to lock in. Fix some of the game breaking bugs, and don't care about the small ones until later. You have to fix: backpacks not working, sell not working, being able to clip things on the wall or stands together, and fix this one most importantly: YOU CAN GRAB GUNS AND ITEMS OUT OF PEOPLE'S HANDS AND SHOOT THEM WITH IT. They won't know you have their item, because they still see it in their hand. They are just shooting themselves on their screen. You also fall out of the map when you die. The owner of this game is really nice, too. He gave everyone 100k for compensation. Do not listen to anyone that is trying to defame this game. This game is only on day 1, remember that. It has a lot of potential, and I think if the developers lock in, we can make this work.",
